      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINOS NZ (6) joins Jason Grimson for his return from a successful stint in Perth where he won three times at Gloucester Park. He was a Group 2 winner when trained in NSW previously and owns strong statistics at both the circuit and the distance. GLITTER AINT GOLD (2) is finding it hard to break through but continues to race well, making it four placings on the trot when he led and boxed on for a 1.4m second last week. Drops to a distance he is yet to win at but draws to advantage. FRANCO NOVELIST NZ (3) won from wider than this two back before he kept chasing to place last week. Racing well and draws for another good showing. JAY OK (1) has been solid from wider barriers of late so should get every chance from the ace draw.",
